Package com.olap3.cubeexplorer.measures.graph

Class NOGraph<E extends java.lang.Comparable<E>,​N extends java.lang.Comparable<N>>

  • java.lang.Object
    • com.olap3.cubeexplorer.measures.graph.NOGraph<E,​N>
  • Type Parameters:
    E - type of edge values
    N - type of node labels, must implement comparable
    All Implemented Interfaces:
    Graph<E,​N>
    public class NOGraph<E extends java.lang.Comparable<E>,​N extends java.lang.Comparable<N>>
extends java.lang.Object
implements Graph<E,​N>
    Non oriented Graph class. When querying the graph with two nodes N1 and N2, the smallest of the two according to Comparable is taken first to really perform the query ( (N1,N2) if N1 < N2 else (N2,N1) ).
